P\left(E_{1}\wedge E_{2}\right)=P\left(E_{2}\mid E_{1}\right)P\left(E_{1}\right)
P\left(E_{1}\right)=\dfrac{4}{10}
P\left(E_{2}\mid E_{1}\right)=\dfrac{3}{9}
P\left(E_{1}\wedge E_{2}\right)=\dfrac{12}{90}=\dfrac{2}{15}
P\left(E_{1}\wedge E_{2}^{c}\right)=P\left(E_{2}^{c}\mid E_{1}\right)P\left(E_{1}\right)=\dfrac{6}{9}\times\dfrac{4}{10}=\dfrac{4}{15}
P\left(E_{1}\wedge E_{2}^{c}\right)+P\left(E_{1}^{c}\wedge E_{2}\right)=\dfrac{8}{15}
1-\dfrac{2}{15}-\dfrac{8}{15}=\dfrac{1}{3}
